Terminal operator, SIFAX Group, has provided free dental and medical care to 205 residents of Ibadan at the annual Taiwo Afolabi Free Rural Dental Outreach. According to a statement, the outreach organised by the University of Ibadan’s Association of Dental Students was sponsored by the firm. In a statement, the Group Head, Corporate Communication, SIFAX, Muyiwa Akande, was quoted as saying, “Some of the services the beneficiaries enjoyed were Body Mass Index measurement, blood pressure test, random blood glucose measurement, blood pressure measurement, dental clerking amongst others.” According to the firm, traders were the largest beneficiaries of the medical outreach. The President, University of Ibadan Dental Students Association, Olalekan Efunkunle, added that the aim of the outreach was to create oral health awareness and promote good oral health hygiene in society.  Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com